<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-17T15:23:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="741" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d741">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.4016/49: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi><note n="6" xml:id="d741fn6">Forwarded by
                                    the Commission to Negotiate Peace as No. 2143.</note></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1919-05-17T16:23:00-04:00" notBefore="1919-05-04T00:00:00+03:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        May 17, 1919, 4.23 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>9. Department’s 1797 [<hi rend="italic">1727</hi>] April 25, 2 p.m.,
                                received May 3, both reports referred to in Department’s telegram
                                inaccurate. Committee composed of both Poles and Jews appointed by
                                Polish Diet has <pb facs="0834" n="749" xml:id="pg_749"/> just
                                returned from making investigation on the ground. Some 400 pages of
                                testimony taken and now being digested. I am promised full reply as
                                soon as it is ready and shall report further.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>